answers.answer: The symptoms you speak of do indicate diabetic nerve damage but if your blood sugar tests normal it may be something else. i would recommend getting tested by primary care physician to check for some other kind of nerve damage or diabetes that didn't show up at your last test. i wish you luck and if it turns out to be some other kind of nerve damage that diabetes i hope it can be repaired easily. But for many diabetics the first sign often is the nerve damage.

question: Hi!  I am a 21 year old female, I experience numbness and tingling in my feet, but that's all.  I'm almost 100 pounds overweight so I'm concerned about diabetes.  i havent had any testing done, except I had my blood sugar tested recently and it was normal.  Can you tell me what else it could be, or if it's likely I do have diabetes, based on this information?  I dont drink a lot, have dry skin, feel dizzy/tired whatever.  Just the tingling numbness!  Thank you!
title: Tingling numbess-only symptom
